---
description: Software architecture standards for maintainable production systems
alwaysApply: true
---

# Architecture Principles

- Prefer clear boundaries: UI, application logic, domain logic, infrastructure.
- Keep modules cohesive and loosely coupled.
- Define explicit contracts between components (types/interfaces/schemas).
- Avoid hidden cross-layer dependencies and circular imports.

# Change Strategy

- Prefer incremental, reversible changes over large risky rewrites.
- Preserve backward compatibility unless user approves a breaking change.
- Include migration notes when behavior or interfaces change.

# Operational Readiness

- Ensure error paths are explicit and user-safe.
- Prefer deterministic behavior and idempotent operations when possible.
- Add observability hooks where useful (structured errors, actionable logs, measurable checkpoints).
